benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Retrieve bundle tags

covered: Valid Request: Happy path with 200 and application/json verified.
Empty Response: Scenario for bundles with no tags returns empty array.
Query Parameters: includedDeleted default/true/false and audit=FULL/MINIMAL combinations covered; invalid audit value validated as 400; unexpected params covered.
Input Validation: Invalid bundleId format returns 400; SQL-injection-like payload handled (400/422).
Authorization: Missing and invalid auth tokens return 401.
Resilience: API unavailable and slow dependency scenarios covered with 503/504 handling.
Performance: Large result set, concurrency, and resource utilization scenarios included.
Regression/Backward compatibility: Scenarios ensuring deleted tags excluded when includedDeleted=false and default audit behavior when omitted.
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios validating pagination behavior for large datasets (if supported).
Caching Behavior: No validation of ETag/Last-Modified or Cache-Control headers; no If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since flow (304).
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios to verify 429 Too Many Requests and Retry-After headers.
Authorization Granularity: No 403 Forbidden scenario for authenticated but unauthorized user/tenant.
Content Negotiation: No tests for Accept headers and 406 Not Acceptable behavior.
Contract Validation: No strict schema validation of Tag object against definitions (types/required fields).
Server Error Handling: No coverage for unexpected 5xx (e.g., internal server error) from backend while service is up.
Audit Defaults: No explicit test for audit=NONE behavior (default) beyond omission; no combination tests for includedDeleted with audit=MINIMAL/NONE.
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios for large tag sets (e.g., page/size params if available); if not supported, add a negative test proving pagination params are rejected.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/Last-Modified and Cache-Control on 200; follow-up request with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since expecting 304.
Introduce rate limiting tests: burst requests exceeding limits should trigger 429 and validate Retry-After header.
Add 403 Forbidden scenario to cover authorization at resource/tenant scope (authenticated but not permitted).
Add content negotiation tests: set Accept to application/json (200) and to unsupported type (406).
Implement response contract tests validating Tag schema (required fields, types, enum values) across scenarios.
Include a controlled 5xx simulation (e.g., forced backend failure) to verify error body shape and headers for server errors.
Add explicit audit=NONE scenario and combination cases with includedDeleted to complete the query-parameter matrix.
Extend header checks (Content-Type, charset) consistently across success and error responses, and verify error body format.
